Boil a full #kettle{}.

When boiling, pour the water into a large #saucepan {}with 1/4 tsp @salt{} on high heat. Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, heat in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

When the pan is hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the mince cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}.

Trim the @Green Beans{80%g} and cut into thirds.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @Salted Peanuts{25%g}.

Once the beef is browned, add the shallot and green beans to the pan and stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @Massaman Curry Paste{50%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Ketjap Manis{50%ml}, @Sugar{1/2} and @Water{75%ml} for the sauce (see ingredients for amount) into the pan, then bring to the boil.

Simmer until the sauce has thickened and is sticky, ~{3-4%minutes}.

When ready, fluff up with rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sticky beef and sprinkle over the chopped peanuts for those who'd like them. Enjoy!